noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Measured Transceiver Delay can be read out from TRV_DELAY register via SW.
 Transceiver delay readable from TRV_DELAY register is shadowed and this
 shadowed value is changed upon the end of Transceiver Delay measurement.
 Therefore if SW reads Transceiver Delay during measurement, it will read
 previous measured value.
 New value will be read only after the end of current measurement.
 To read proper value of Transceiver Delay from TRV_DELAY, at least one
 CAN FD frame must have been transmitted during previous operation, otherwise
 0 will be read from TRV_DELAY register.
